summary:
Favorite lines from every song on Red. 
"So you were never a saint, and I loved in shades of wrong. We learn to live with the...
body:
Favorite lines from every song on Red.

“So you were never a saint, and I loved in shades of wrong. We learn to live with the pain, mosaic broken hearts.”

“Remembering him comes in flashbacks and echoes. I tell myself it’s time now, gotta let go.”

“All we are is skin and bone trained to get along. Forever going with the flow, but you’re friction.”

“And the saddest fear comes creeping in that he never loved me or her or anyone or anything.”

“And I might be okay but I’m not fine at all.”

“It feels like a perfect night for breakfast at midnight.”

“And I bet it never ever occurred to you that I can’t say hello to you and risk another good-bye.”

“You call me up again tonight but this time I’m telling you, I’m telling you we are never ever ever getting back together.”

“No one else is gonna love me when I get mad.”

“This is the last time I’m asking you why you break my heart in the blink of an eye.”

“Spinning like a girl in a brand new dress. We had this big wide city all to ourselves. We blocked the noise with the sound of ‘I need you’ and for the first time I had something to lose.”

“Distance. Timing. Breakdown. Fighting. Silence. Train runs off its track.”

“Cause now my name is up in lights, but I think you got it right.”

“Your eyes looked like coming home.”

“Cant remember what song he was playing when we walked in the night we snuck into a yacht club party pretending to be a duchess and a prince.”

“And for the first time, what’s past is past.”

“What do you do when the one who means the most to you is the one who didnt show?”

“I dont wanna miss you like this.”

“I feel a responsibility to do what’s upstanding and right.”

summary: The Red era is so magical to me, when I made a Taylor Swift orientated Tumblr it was after the release of Safe and Sound and...
body:
The Red era is so magical to me, when I made a Taylor Swift orientated Tumblr it was after the release of Safe and Sound and Eyes Open (I know no one will remember me being playingsoldiers–justpretending) so the lead up to Red and the release was the first album I was on here to get excited over. 
My album arrived early (Back before Amazon prime next day delivery) so I got to listen to the album 3 days prior, despite people panicking and begging people not to listen to the music before Taylor wanted us too 

6 years ago I was 17, had just started going to parties and drinking and I would always put wanegbt or Starlight onto the playlists and had weird dance routines to the songs with my friends. It was the first album that I bought myself and bought multiple versions of it was the start of an incredible journey and honestly the autumn of the release of Red is one of my strongest memories, I remember the feeling of hearing all the songs and listening to nothing else for about 6 months. Red Tour was also the first tour I was ever able to go to, travelling down to London to sit in nose bleed seats, I’m talking the very top only to get upgraded to front row, truly the best feeling and I hope @taylornation knows how appreciative myself and my friends are

sorry this was a long post and I know you all have given up. I just want to say Red is that bitch and stop sleeping on The Last Time 
Thank you @taylorswift
